	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm not averse to longer extensions so long as they're single-part. One of my favorite PC games (which becomes legal in 2019*) uses <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">.smzip</tt>, and the 3D modeling program I used for the title screen of <em>RHDE</em> uses <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">.blend</tt>. I'll probably go with <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">.dmchr</tt> or something similar.<br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: 85%; line-height: normal">* Right now, StepMania is in the same sort of legal limbo as LAME and x264: free software covered by software patents in some major markets.</span>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


